1
00:00:40,163 --> 00:00:44,202
Minister: Do you, Ethan, take Julia
to be your lawful wedded wife?

2
00:00:44,293 --> 00:00:45,293
I do.

3
00:00:45,377 --> 00:00:50,246
To have, to hold,
to love, Cherish, honor, and protect?

4
00:00:50,340 --> 00:00:51,796
I do.

5
00:00:51,883 --> 00:00:56,001
Minister: To shield from terrors known
and unknown?

6
00:00:56,096 --> 00:00:59,179
- To lie, to deceive...
“what?

7
00:00:59,266 --> 00:01:03,259
To live a double life,
to fail to prevent her abduction,

8
00:01:03,353 --> 00:01:06,971
erase her identity,
force her into hiding,

9
00:01:07,065 --> 00:01:08,521
take away all she has known...

10
00:01:08,609 --> 00:01:09,609
Stop.

11
00:01:09,693 --> 00:01:11,254
In a selfish, futile,
fleeting attempt...

12
00:01:11,278 --> 00:01:12,358
Stop.

13
00:01:12,446 --> 00:01:14,983
to escape your own true self?

14
00:01:15,073 --> 00:01:16,108
Please, stop.

15
00:01:16,199 --> 00:01:18,531
And, Julia, do you choose to accept?

16
00:01:18,619 --> 00:01:19,619
Don't.

17
00:01:19,953 --> 00:01:22,160
- I do.
- No.

18
00:01:23,915 --> 00:01:25,746
You should have killed me, Ethan.

19
00:01:25,834 --> 00:01:27,415
(Explosion in distance)

20
00:01:32,674 --> 00:01:33,709
(Sighs)

21
00:01:37,929 --> 00:01:39,089
(Knock at door)

22
00:01:42,684 --> 00:01:44,515
(Thunder rumbling)

23
00:01:44,936 --> 00:01:46,767
(Knocking continues)

24
00:01:54,488 --> 00:01:56,820
Fate whispers to the warrior...

25
00:01:57,574 --> 00:01:59,314
Ethan: A storm is coming.

26
00:01:59,660 --> 00:02:01,651
Deliveryman:
And the warrior whispers back...

27
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:05,661
I am the storm.

28
00:02:06,083 --> 00:02:07,823
(Thunder rumbling)

29
00:02:33,527 --> 00:02:34,733
(Device beeping)

30
00:02:40,158 --> 00:02:41,898
Man: (On speaker)
Good evening, Mr. hunt.

31
00:02:41,993 --> 00:02:44,200
The anarchist Solomon Lane.

32
00:02:44,454 --> 00:02:46,240
Since you captured him 2 years ago,

33
00:02:46,331 --> 00:02:50,415
his absence from the world stage
has had unintended consequences.

34
00:02:50,502 --> 00:02:52,163
His syndicate of rogue covert operatives

35
00:02:52,254 --> 00:02:54,996
continues to wreak havoc
around the globe.

36
00:02:55,090 --> 00:02:56,955
The CIA's special activities division

37
00:02:57,050 --> 00:03:00,167
has relentlessly hunted Lane's
elite network of hosliles.

38
00:03:00,262 --> 00:03:02,594
But many remain unknown and at large.

39
00:03:02,848 --> 00:03:04,804
The remnants of this
extremist splinter cell

40
00:03:04,891 --> 00:03:07,303
refer to themselves as "the apostles.”

41
00:03:08,854 --> 00:03:11,470
they have since adopted
a policy of terror-for-hire,

42
00:03:11,565 --> 00:03:13,806
making them an even greater threat.

43
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:16,232
They are responsible for
the recent smallpox outbreak

44
00:03:16,319 --> 00:03:17,650
in Indian-controlled kashmir,

45
00:03:17,738 --> 00:03:20,024
along the borders of China and Pakistan,

46
00:03:20,115 --> 00:03:22,481
threatening one-third
of the world’s population.

47
00:03:22,576 --> 00:03:24,567
The epidemic is being contained,

48
00:03:24,661 --> 00:03:26,117
but intelligence would indicate

49
00:03:26,204 --> 00:03:30,573
that a new client has hired the apostles
for a more ambitious operation.

50
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:32,407
They have been contacted by this man,

51
00:03:32,502 --> 00:03:36,211
an unidentified extremist
known only by the code name John lark,

52
00:03:36,298 --> 00:03:38,380
author of this apocalyptic manifesto

53
00:03:38,467 --> 00:03:41,880
calling for the destruction
of the current world order.

54
00:03:41,970 --> 00:03:44,757
It is believed lark is responsible
for the disappearance

55
00:03:44,848 --> 00:03:48,011
of Norwegian nuclear weapons
specialist nils delbruuk.

56
00:03:48,101 --> 00:03:50,183
Dr. delbruuk's security
clearance was revoked

57
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:53,182
after he expressed
fiercely anti-religious views.

58
00:03:53,273 --> 00:03:55,264
Meanwhile, the apostles
have been in contact

59
00:03:55,358 --> 00:03:57,599
with elements of
the eastern European underworld,

60
00:03:57,694 --> 00:04:00,060
who are in possession
of three plutonium cores

61
00:04:00,155 --> 00:04:02,897
stolen from a missile base
in eastern Russia.

62
00:04:03,575 --> 00:04:05,816
This would indicate that
John lark and the apostles

63
00:04:05,911 --> 00:04:09,745
are working together
to acquire functioning nuclear weapons.

64
00:04:10,248 --> 00:04:12,614
Nest estimates that a man
with delbruuk’'s knowledge,

65
00:04:12,709 --> 00:04:13,994
using the materials in play,

66
00:04:14,085 --> 00:04:18,454
could complete three nuclear weapons
in as little as 72 hours.

67
00:04:18,548 --> 00:04:20,254
These devices would be man-portable

68
00:04:20,342 --> 00:04:22,833
and deployable anywhere
on earth overnight.

69
00:04:23,303 --> 00:04:25,419
In the hands of John lark
and the apostles,

70
00:04:25,514 --> 00:04:27,800
these weapons represent
an unprecedented threat

71
00:04:27,891 --> 00:04:29,597
to countless millions.

72
00:04:30,101 --> 00:04:32,387
Your mission,
should you choose to accept it,

73
00:04:32,479 --> 00:04:35,061
is to prevent the apostles
from acquiring plutonium

74
00:04:35,148 --> 00:04:37,639
using any means at your disposal.

75
00:04:37,943 --> 00:04:41,481
If you or any members of your imf team
are caught or killed,

76
00:04:41,571 --> 00:04:44,608
the secretary will disavow
any knowledge of your actions.

77
00:04:44,699 --> 00:04:45,779
Good luck, Ethan.

78
00:04:45,867 --> 00:04:48,984
This message will
self-destruct in five seconds.

79
00:04:50,539 --> 00:04:51,949
(Rain pattering)

80
00:04:52,499 --> 00:04:53,579
(Sizzles)

81
00:05:04,135 --> 00:05:05,466
He's late.

82
00:05:05,971 --> 00:05:08,587
- He's never late.
- He'll be here.

83
00:05:08,682 --> 00:05:10,047
I don't like it.

84
00:05:10,475 --> 00:05:13,717
Something about this guy
just really gives me the creeps.

85
00:05:13,812 --> 00:05:15,803
Okay, just relax.

86
00:05:15,897 --> 00:05:17,228
I'm relaxed.

87
00:05:17,315 --> 00:05:18,395
You don't sound relaxed.

88
00:05:18,483 --> 00:05:19,877
Luther, does he sound relaxed to you?

89
00:05:19,901 --> 00:05:21,857
(Chuckles) He sounds terrified.

90
00:05:21,945 --> 00:05:24,549
Benji: Please, I'm not terrified.
I just have a bad feeling is all.

91
00:05:24,573 --> 00:05:26,313
Luther: / thought you said
you were relaxed.

92
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:29,900
It's entirely possible to be relaxed
and extremely uneasy at the same time.

93
00:05:29,995 --> 00:05:31,826
- No, it's not.
You do it all the time.

94
00:05:31,913 --> 00:05:33,494
- No, I don't.
- Yes, you do.

95
00:05:33,582 --> 00:05:34,697
No, he doesn't.

96
00:05:34,791 --> 00:05:36,727
I'm supposed to believe that
you are perfectly relaxed,

97
00:05:36,751 --> 00:05:38,161
- right here, now...
- Beniji.

98
00:05:38,253 --> 00:05:39,397
In a dark alleyway, waiting to buy

99
00:05:39,421 --> 00:05:41,582
black-market plutonium
from a psychopath.

100
00:05:41,673 --> 00:05:43,334
Benji, I won't let anything
happen to you.

101
00:05:43,425 --> 00:05:44,835
- (Scoffs) Okay.
Luther: See, Benji,

102
00:05:44,926 --> 00:05:46,257
you're perfectly safe.

103
00:05:46,344 --> 00:05:48,209
That's easy for you to say,
you're in the Van.

104
00:05:48,305 --> 00:05:50,116
Well, you wanted to be
in the field, tough guy.

105
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:52,176
And tonight, Luther,
I would like to be in the Van!

106
00:05:52,267 --> 00:05:53,867
- (Tires squeal in distance)
- He's here.

107
00:05:53,894 --> 00:05:55,430
Oh, god. (Clears throat)

108
00:06:02,527 --> 00:06:03,983
(Car doors opening)

109
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:07,820
(Car doors close)

110
00:06:10,577 --> 00:06:12,158
Ethan: Have that money ready, Luther.

111
00:06:12,412 --> 00:06:13,492
Luther: Copy.

112
00:06:18,251 --> 00:06:19,582
Ethan, do you copy?

113
00:06:19,753 --> 00:06:21,243
Do you copy?

114
00:06:22,923 --> 00:06:23,958
(Gasps)

115
00:06:33,850 --> 00:06:36,182
Are we finally gonna
do this or not?

116
00:06:42,025 --> 00:06:46,359
I have survived in this business
with the help of a voice in my head.

117
00:06:48,281 --> 00:06:51,523
This voice is never wrong.
And whenever I meet you,

118
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,821
it tells me the same thing.

119
00:06:54,871 --> 00:06:55,871
What's that?

120
00:06:56,790 --> 00:06:58,121
Nothing.

121
00:07:03,004 --> 00:07:06,667
I'm here to do business.
Tell the voice to flip a coin.

122
00:07:34,119 --> 00:07:35,575
(Device beeping)

123
00:07:35,704 --> 00:07:37,194
(Device trilling)

124
00:07:38,373 --> 00:07:39,453
What's that?

125
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,824
This is a beryllium rod,
which is causing

126
00:07:41,918 --> 00:07:44,830
a reaction with the plutonium
inside the core.

127
00:07:45,463 --> 00:07:46,578
(Continues trilling)

128
00:07:53,722 --> 00:07:55,053
That's them.

129
00:07:57,976 --> 00:07:59,056
The money?

130
00:08:00,395 --> 00:08:01,726
The money.

131
00:08:04,566 --> 00:08:05,897
Bring the money.

132
00:08:18,079 --> 00:08:20,070
Luther, bring the money.

133
00:08:28,757 --> 00:08:30,748
We're gonna need
that money, Luther.

134
00:08:31,259 --> 00:08:32,669
Kill them.

135
00:08:32,761 --> 00:08:34,092
(Gunshots)

136
00:08:34,554 --> 00:08:36,135
- (Shoutys)
(Gunshots)

137
00:08:37,932 --> 00:08:39,263
I got it!

138
00:08:43,271 --> 00:08:44,511
Luther, do you copy?

139
00:08:44,731 --> 00:08:45,731
Luther!

140
00:08:45,899 --> 00:08:47,230
Luther, come in.

141
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,140
Man: Luther's not here right now.

142
00:08:49,235 --> 00:08:52,568
What can the apostles
do for you, hunt?

143
00:08:52,655 --> 00:08:54,941
- What do you want?
- You're boxed in, hunt.

144
00:08:55,617 --> 00:08:58,529
Give us the plutonium
and walk away.

145
00:08:58,870 --> 00:09:00,656
Benji, get the car.

146
00:09:00,747 --> 00:09:02,328
- L don't think I can do that.
- Beniji.

147
00:09:02,415 --> 00:09:04,121
Get the car.

148
00:09:08,254 --> 00:09:09,494
(Car engine starts)

149
00:09:11,841 --> 00:09:13,251
(Gun firing)

150
00:09:20,350 --> 00:09:21,430
(Grunts)

151
00:09:24,437 --> 00:09:26,348
Man: We'll make you a deal, hunt.

152
00:09:26,439 --> 00:09:30,273
Give us the plutonium
and we won't kill your friend.

153
00:09:33,488 --> 00:09:35,774
Don't you do it, Ethan! Not for me!

154
00:09:48,586 --> 00:09:50,497
- (Panting)
- Man: I'm gonna count to three.

155
00:09:51,381 --> 00:09:52,381
One.

156
00:09:54,134 --> 00:09:55,795
- Two.
- Luther...

157
00:09:56,636 --> 00:09:57,967
- 'M sorry.
- Three.

158
00:10:09,190 --> 00:10:10,225
(Groans softly)

159
00:10:11,109 --> 00:10:13,065
(Breathing heavily)

160
00:10:13,236 --> 00:10:15,443
I'm sorry.
I didn't know what else to do.

161
00:10:15,530 --> 00:10:16,895
(Strained) We're good.

162
00:10:18,908 --> 00:10:20,489
(Coughing)

163
00:10:20,702 --> 00:10:22,613
- You okay?
- I should be dead.

164
00:10:22,954 --> 00:10:24,615
We should all be dead.

165
00:10:26,457 --> 00:10:27,947
Why aren't we?

166
00:10:28,626 --> 00:10:29,991
Where's the plutonium?

167
00:10:42,307 --> 00:10:43,638
It's gone.

168
00:10:48,062 --> 00:10:49,540
Wolf blitzer: (On TV)
If you're just joining us,

169
00:10:49,564 --> 00:10:53,853
three massive explosions
have gone off simultaneously

170
00:10:56,654 --> 00:10:59,817
this image is live in Rome,
looking toward the Vatican

171
00:10:59,908 --> 00:11:02,240
and is as close as our cameras can get.

172
00:11:02,327 --> 00:11:05,444
It is believed that
the pope was in residence

173
00:11:05,538 --> 00:11:06,778
at the time of the blast.

174
00:11:06,873 --> 00:11:10,957
Also live, we're looking at Jerusalem
from just outside the city.

175
00:11:11,044 --> 00:11:13,330
Also live, the holy city of mecca

176
00:11:13,421 --> 00:11:15,958
from the USS Ronald Reagan
in the red sea

177
00:11:16,049 --> 00:11:18,165
off the coast of Saudi Arabia.

178
00:11:18,259 --> 00:11:20,250
Radiation has been detected,

179
00:11:20,345 --> 00:11:23,382
indicating that
nuclear weapons were used

180
00:11:23,473 --> 00:11:25,259
in these unspeakable attacks.

181
00:11:25,350 --> 00:11:27,511
Luther: Ethan, it's time.

182
00:11:27,602 --> 00:11:29,038
No word on casualties yet,
but we can assume

183
00:11:29,062 --> 00:11:30,723
the death toll is catastrophic.

184
00:11:30,897 --> 00:11:33,138
Early reports suggest
the weapons used

185
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:35,724
would require
highly specialized knowledge

186
00:11:35,818 --> 00:11:37,433
that very few people possess.

187
00:11:38,029 --> 00:11:42,693
The question now is who would attack
all three of these holy sites? And why?

188
00:11:43,117 --> 00:11:46,200
The attacks occurred
at precisely the same moment,

189
00:11:46,287 --> 00:11:47,447
just over an hour ago,

190
00:11:47,747 --> 00:11:49,362
at 4:00 A.M. eastern time.

191
00:11:49,457 --> 00:11:51,018
- Within minutes of the attack...
- (Chuckling)

192
00:11:51,042 --> 00:11:53,408
Congress ordered
an emergency recess

193
00:11:53,503 --> 00:11:55,164
and the capitol building
was evacuated.

194
00:11:55,255 --> 00:11:58,042
The president left Washington
on air force one.

195
00:11:58,132 --> 00:12:00,418
The white house has declared
a state of emergency,

196
00:12:00,510 --> 00:12:02,796
placing the military on highest alert.

197
00:12:02,887 --> 00:12:05,003
Would you excuse us, please?

198
00:12:06,891 --> 00:12:08,301
Dr. delbruuk.

199
00:12:08,434 --> 00:12:09,924
(Machine beeping)

200
00:12:10,061 --> 00:12:11,346
Ethan: We know who you are.

201
00:12:11,437 --> 00:12:14,224
We read the manifesto,
we found your lab.

202
00:12:16,359 --> 00:12:17,394
(Sniffles)

203
00:12:17,610 --> 00:12:19,601
(Indistinct announcement
on pa)

204
00:12:24,784 --> 00:12:26,115
"There has never been peace

205
00:12:26,202 --> 00:12:28,193
"without first a great suffering.

206
00:12:28,288 --> 00:12:30,654
"The greater the suffering,
the greater the peace."

207
00:12:30,915 --> 00:12:33,076
See, this will unite them, hmm?

208
00:12:34,502 --> 00:12:36,834
When they read this manifesto,
they'll all understand.

209
00:12:36,921 --> 00:12:39,628
Nobody's gonna read
that manifesto, ever.

210
00:12:39,716 --> 00:12:41,581
I can promise you that.

211
00:12:41,676 --> 00:12:43,007
Delbruuk: What day is it?

212
00:12:43,177 --> 00:12:44,667
How long have I been here?

213
00:12:44,846 --> 00:12:46,382
What's the last thing you remember?

214
00:12:47,307 --> 00:12:49,514
(Stammers) I was driving.

215
00:12:51,519 --> 00:12:52,519
Someone hit me.

216
00:12:52,603 --> 00:12:54,264
That was two weeks ago.

217
00:12:55,064 --> 00:12:56,270
- Two weeks?
- Two weeks.

218
00:12:56,607 --> 00:12:58,188
Luther: This is yours, isn't it?

219
00:12:58,693 --> 00:13:00,684
It's how lark communicated with you.

220
00:13:00,778 --> 00:13:03,235
- (Sniffles) Lark?
- Ethan: John lark.

221
00:13:03,323 --> 00:13:05,564
- We know all about him.
- You know nothing.

222
00:13:05,658 --> 00:13:08,338
Luther: There's information in this
phone that could lead us to him.

223
00:13:08,369 --> 00:13:10,075
And you have the passcode.

224
00:13:10,163 --> 00:13:12,449
You think lark is the enemy, hmm?

225
00:13:13,291 --> 00:13:14,872
But you,

226
00:13:14,959 --> 00:13:17,996
well, whoever you are,
you are the enemy.

227
00:13:18,087 --> 00:13:19,668
You're why the system survives.

228
00:13:20,548 --> 00:13:22,709
- Why the suffering goes on.
- Shut up!

229
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,212
We don't care about you.
We want lark.

230
00:13:25,303 --> 00:13:26,543
What if we make a deal?

231
00:13:26,637 --> 00:13:28,037
Ethan: No, there's no deal, Luther.

232
00:13:28,556 --> 00:13:29,966
Step outside.

233
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:32,386
Give me five minutes with this guy.

234
00:13:32,477 --> 00:13:34,968
Ethan, I can't let you do that.
That's not who we are.

235
00:13:35,063 --> 00:13:37,600
Then maybe we need to reconsider that.

236
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:40,022
What if they read
the manifesto on the air?

237
00:13:40,109 --> 00:13:41,109
What? You can do that?

238
00:13:41,194 --> 00:13:42,775
We can do it with a phone call.

239
00:13:44,530 --> 00:13:46,691
Delbruuk: Well, if he reads
lark's manifesto...

240
00:13:46,783 --> 00:13:47,783
No.

241
00:13:47,867 --> 00:13:49,573
(Laughing) I'll give you the passcode.

242
00:13:50,411 --> 00:13:51,651
Luther: Ethan! Ethan!

243
00:13:51,788 --> 00:13:53,449
(Laughing)
- Think, Ethan.

244
00:13:53,539 --> 00:13:55,325
Think of the greater good, please.

245
00:13:55,708 --> 00:13:57,198
Yeah, you do that.

246
00:13:58,836 --> 00:13:59,916
(Grunts)

247
00:14:01,839 --> 00:14:03,670
(Continues laughing)

248
00:14:04,842 --> 00:14:05,877
Hmm?

249
00:14:06,177 --> 00:14:08,168
(Indistinct announcement on pa)

250
00:14:10,973 --> 00:14:11,973
Ethan: Sir.

251
00:14:12,558 --> 00:14:14,219
No, he won't cooperate.

252
00:14:15,103 --> 00:14:18,061
Yes, sir. If we read the manifesto

253
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:20,600
on the air.

254
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:24,600
I'm sorry, sir.

255
00:14:26,155 --> 00:14:27,361
(Line disconnects)

256
00:14:31,953 --> 00:14:34,695
Wolf blitzer: (On TV)
Trading and global markets plummeted.

257
00:14:34,789 --> 00:14:39,704
Stand by. I'm told we're about
fo get some additional information.

258
00:14:40,378 --> 00:14:44,291
I've just been handed a document
from nils delbruuk,

259
00:14:44,382 --> 00:14:46,338
a nuclear weapons specialist

260
00:14:46,426 --> 00:14:49,463
who claims to have built the weapons
used in these attacks.

261
00:14:49,971 --> 00:14:53,680
I've been asked to read
this manifesto in its entirety.

262
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:55,760
"There has never been peace

263
00:14:55,852 --> 00:14:57,513
"without first a great suffering.

264
00:14:57,854 --> 00:14:59,845
"The greater the suffering,
the greater the peace.

265
00:14:59,939 --> 00:15:00,974
(Laughing)

266
00:15:01,065 --> 00:15:03,977
"As mankind is drawn
to his self-destruction

267
00:15:04,068 --> 00:15:05,808
"like a moth to the candle,

268
00:15:05,903 --> 00:15:07,768
"the so-called defenders of peace,

269
00:15:07,864 --> 00:15:10,697
"the church, the government, the law,

270
00:15:10,783 --> 00:15:13,775
"work tirelessly
to save humanity from itself.”

271
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:15,406
it's not gonna help you now.

272
00:15:15,496 --> 00:15:17,282
"But by averting disaster,

273
00:15:17,373 --> 00:15:18,988
"they serve to delay a peace...”

274
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:20,289
what's done is done.

275
00:15:20,376 --> 00:15:23,459
"That can only come through
an inevitable baptism of fire.

276
00:15:23,546 --> 00:15:26,754
"The suffering I bring you
is not the beginning of the end.

277
00:15:26,841 --> 00:15:27,921
"It is the beginning

278
00:15:28,009 --> 00:15:29,361
"of a greater mutual understanding...”

279
00:15:29,385 --> 00:15:30,716
did we get it?

280
00:15:31,762 --> 00:15:33,162
Wolf blitzer: “it is the first step

281
00:15:33,222 --> 00:15:34,658
"toward the ultimate
brotherhood of man.”

282
00:15:34,682 --> 00:15:35,797
we got it.

283
00:15:35,892 --> 00:15:37,382
"The suffering I bring you

284
00:15:37,477 --> 00:15:39,013
"is the bridge to ultimate peace."

285
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:40,770
Go.

286
00:15:40,938 --> 00:15:42,018
(Thudding)

287
00:15:49,989 --> 00:15:51,104
(Gasps)

288
00:15:54,410 --> 00:15:56,071
Did we get it?

289
00:15:56,162 --> 00:15:57,743
Of course we got it.

290
00:16:06,172 --> 00:16:07,503
I told you we'd get it.

291
00:16:08,257 --> 00:16:09,918
I... I don't understand.

292
00:16:10,218 --> 00:16:12,174
The attacks didn't happen?

293
00:16:12,261 --> 00:16:15,970
The car accident you were in,
that was an hour ago.

294
00:16:16,057 --> 00:16:17,843
I was driving the other car.

295
00:16:18,643 --> 00:16:20,099
Ethan: What's done is done,

296
00:16:20,186 --> 00:16:21,926
when we say it's done.

297
00:16:23,147 --> 00:16:25,138
(Mission: Impossible theme playing)

298
00:17:36,053 --> 00:17:37,053
Sir.

299
00:17:37,638 --> 00:17:40,175
That phone you unlocked led us
to a server in Iceland

300
00:17:40,266 --> 00:17:42,131
where we managed to
decrypt a communiqué

301
00:17:42,226 --> 00:17:44,808
between John lark
and this woman:

302
00:17:44,895 --> 00:17:47,352
Alana mitsopolis,
activist and philanthropist,

303
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,555
whose charity work

304
00:17:48,649 --> 00:17:50,085
has earned her
the nickname the white widow.

305
00:17:50,109 --> 00:17:53,727
It's all a front for her real trade:
Arms dealing, money laundering.

306
00:17:53,821 --> 00:17:56,358
Extensive political connections
provide her with protection.

307
00:17:56,449 --> 00:17:57,884
Lark and the widow
are meeting tonight

308
00:17:57,908 --> 00:18:00,991
to negotiate delivery
of an unspecified package,

309
00:18:01,078 --> 00:18:03,945
which we can only assume
is our missing plutonium.

310
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:07,032
They'll make contact in a private lounge
at the grand palais in Paris

311
00:18:07,126 --> 00:18:08,616
during her annual
fundraising event.

312
00:18:08,711 --> 00:18:09,917
The details are in the file.

313
00:18:10,004 --> 00:18:11,231
If lark isn't there by midnight,

314
00:18:11,255 --> 00:18:13,211
the widow will leave

315
00:18:13,299 --> 00:18:14,979
and sell the package
to the highest bidder.

316
00:18:15,009 --> 00:18:18,547
Which gives you
two hours from now to find lark.

317
00:18:18,638 --> 00:18:20,970
Sir, I think there's something
you need to know.

318
00:18:21,057 --> 00:18:22,672
I'm gonna stop you right there.

319
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:25,509
You had a terrible choice
to make in Berlin:

320
00:18:25,603 --> 00:18:27,309
Recover the plutonium or save your team.

321
00:18:27,396 --> 00:18:29,356
You chose your team,
and now the world is at risk.

322
00:18:30,524 --> 00:18:33,186
Some flaw deep in your core being

323
00:18:33,277 --> 00:18:36,690
simply won't allow you to choose
between one life and millions.

324
00:18:36,781 --> 00:18:38,396
You see that as a sign of weakness.

325
00:18:38,491 --> 00:18:41,107
To me, that's your greatest strength.

326
00:18:41,202 --> 00:18:43,944
It also tells me I can count on you
to cover my ass.

327
00:18:44,038 --> 00:18:45,474
Because coming over here from the CIA

328
00:18:45,498 --> 00:18:47,204
was a lateral move,
some say a step down.

329
00:18:47,291 --> 00:18:48,701
But l did it

330
00:18:49,293 --> 00:18:50,703
because of you.

331
00:18:51,379 --> 00:18:52,869
Don't make me regret it.

332
00:19:05,142 --> 00:19:06,473
Make the call.

333
00:19:10,022 --> 00:19:11,432
Walker: Shut 'em down.

334
00:19:11,982 --> 00:19:13,392
(Plane engines power down)

335
00:19:22,118 --> 00:19:23,428
What do you think you're doing, Erika?

336
00:19:23,452 --> 00:19:24,942
It may be your mission,

337
00:19:25,037 --> 00:19:27,119
but this is the CIA's plane.

338
00:19:27,206 --> 00:19:28,912
It doesn't take off without my say-so.

339
00:19:28,999 --> 00:19:30,239
We don't have time for this.

340
00:19:30,334 --> 00:19:32,199
I have a team in Paris
ready to grab lark

341
00:19:32,294 --> 00:19:33,830
as soon as he leaves the palais.

342
00:19:33,921 --> 00:19:36,788
A g5 standing by
to rendition him to gitmo,

343
00:19:36,882 --> 00:19:38,082
where a waterboard is waiting.

344
00:19:38,134 --> 00:19:41,626
Spend 24 hours we don't have
to pull a confession we can't trust

345
00:19:41,721 --> 00:19:44,884
from a man we haven't
positively identified? No.

346
00:19:44,974 --> 00:19:47,636
We need reliable intelligence,
and we need it now.

347
00:19:47,727 --> 00:19:50,389
This scenario is precisely
why the imf exists!

348
00:19:50,479 --> 00:19:52,845
The imf is Halloween, Alan.

349
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:56,649
A bunch of grown men in rubber masks
playing trick-or-treat.

350
00:19:56,736 --> 00:19:59,193
And if he had held on to
the plutonium in Berlin,

351
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:01,316
we wouldn't be having
this conversation.

352
00:20:01,407 --> 00:20:02,759
Hunley: And his team would be dead.

353
00:20:02,783 --> 00:20:04,739
Yes. They would.

354
00:20:04,827 --> 00:20:06,158
That's the job.

355
00:20:06,245 --> 00:20:09,737
And that's why I want
one of my own men on the scene

356
00:20:09,832 --> 00:20:11,868
to appraise the situation.

357
00:20:12,293 --> 00:20:14,534
Agent Walker,
special activities.

358
00:20:14,628 --> 00:20:17,040
His reputation precedes.

359
00:20:17,131 --> 00:20:18,837
Sloane: You use a scalpel.

360
00:20:19,675 --> 00:20:21,506
I prefer a hammer.

361
00:20:21,594 --> 00:20:22,754
Hunley: The answer is no.

362
00:20:22,845 --> 00:20:25,552
I have operational authority here,
direct from the president.

363
00:20:25,639 --> 00:20:26,908
You have a problem with that,
you take it up with him.

364
00:20:26,932 --> 00:20:30,516
I have already, and he agrees
with me. My man goes

365
00:20:30,603 --> 00:20:32,639
or no one goes.

366
00:20:40,321 --> 00:20:42,687
No one comes between
you and that plutonium.

367
00:20:42,782 --> 00:20:45,819
Not hunt, not his team, not anyone.

368
00:21:04,512 --> 00:21:07,174
Ethan: The white widow has spies
at every level of government.

369
00:21:07,515 --> 00:21:09,676
This plane is posing
as a commercial airliner

370
00:21:09,767 --> 00:21:11,928
so we can jump into France undetected.

371
00:21:12,353 --> 00:21:15,095
The widow's meeting lark
in the vip lounge at midnight.

372
00:21:15,189 --> 00:21:18,181
No one will be admitted without
a pre-issued electronic I.D. Band.

373
00:21:18,734 --> 00:21:20,645
We have acquired
the unique rfid number

374
00:21:20,736 --> 00:21:22,727
for lark's band,
allowing us to locate it

375
00:21:23,447 --> 00:21:24,778
with these.

376
00:21:25,115 --> 00:21:27,356
Find that I.D. Band, you find lark.

377
00:21:28,202 --> 00:21:29,533
Then what?

378
00:21:31,539 --> 00:21:33,530
- Then...
- (Device humming)

379
00:21:34,208 --> 00:21:37,826
I assume his identity
and make contact with the widow.

380
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:39,330
She takes us to the package.

381
00:21:40,089 --> 00:21:42,501
People actually fall for this shit?

382
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:45,833
How do you intend
to make lark cooperate?

383
00:21:47,930 --> 00:21:49,591
I bump him in the crowd.

384
00:21:50,307 --> 00:21:52,673
In ten seconds he'll look like
any other drunk at the party,

385
00:21:52,768 --> 00:21:54,599
incoherent and completely pliable.

386
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:56,226
After I borrow his face,

387
00:21:56,313 --> 00:21:59,193
you walk him out the front door and
hand him to Sloane's extraction team.

388
00:21:59,275 --> 00:22:01,266
You're not getting rid of me
that easily, hunt.

389
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:03,021
That's not what this is about.

390
00:22:03,112 --> 00:22:04,818
Sure itis.

391
00:22:04,905 --> 00:22:07,692
I know you don't want me
on this detail.

392
00:22:07,783 --> 00:22:09,364
But let's face it:

393
00:22:09,451 --> 00:22:11,282
If you'd made
the hard choice in Berlin,

394
00:22:11,370 --> 00:22:12,780
I wouldn't be here.

395
00:22:12,872 --> 00:22:14,203
And if you hadn't gunned down

396
00:22:14,290 --> 00:22:16,372
every syndicate agent
they sent you to find,

397
00:22:16,667 --> 00:22:17,998
I wouldn't be here.

398
00:22:18,627 --> 00:22:20,367
That's right, I know all about you.

399
00:22:20,462 --> 00:22:23,454
You're why we don't have a living
witness who can identify John lark

400
00:22:23,549 --> 00:22:25,255
or the apostles.

401
00:22:25,342 --> 00:22:27,879
If you have a problem
with my methods,

402
00:22:27,970 --> 00:22:29,926
you can always stay behind.

403
00:22:30,014 --> 00:22:33,506
"Your mission, should you
choose to accept it."

404
00:22:33,601 --> 00:22:35,387
Isn't that the thing?

405
00:22:35,477 --> 00:22:36,717
(Alarm blaring)

406
00:22:36,854 --> 00:22:38,814
Pilot: (On intercom)
Two minutes to decompression.

407
00:22:38,939 --> 00:22:42,682
Suit up. The widow is meeting lark
in 30 minutes.

408
00:22:56,165 --> 00:22:57,371
(Air hissing)

409
