We're code blue.

525
00:33:53,738 --> 00:33:55,353
Send sanitation.

526
00:33:56,199 --> 00:33:57,530
North men's room.

527
00:33:59,953 --> 00:34:02,365
You didn't answer my question.
What are you doing here?

528
00:34:02,497 --> 00:34:03,862
(Indistinct chatter)

529
00:34:05,709 --> 00:34:07,415
That's it. Just take it easy.
That's it.

530
00:34:07,502 --> 00:34:09,462
Just keep your head back
until the bleeding stops.

531
00:34:09,546 --> 00:34:10,786
What is it, eh? (Speaks French)

532
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,996
You want some, too?

533
00:34:14,843 --> 00:34:17,004
(In English) You're not here
by accident. Who sent you?

534
00:34:17,262 --> 00:34:18,593
I can't tell you that.

535
00:34:18,680 --> 00:34:19,680
What are you doing?

536
00:34:19,764 --> 00:34:20,992
I have a date with the white widow.

537
00:34:21,016 --> 00:34:23,507
He had a date with the widow.
You look nothing like him.

538
00:34:23,977 --> 00:34:26,218
And now we have to hope
they never met.

539
00:34:26,313 --> 00:34:29,146
- Hope is not a strategy!
- Oh, you must be new.

540
00:34:29,566 --> 00:34:30,566
I have no other choice.

541
00:34:30,650 --> 00:34:32,231
The white widow's our only lead.

542
00:34:32,319 --> 00:34:33,754
I got to be this guy for five minutes.

543
00:34:33,778 --> 00:34:35,564
- Don't do it.
- Ethan: What?

544
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:38,651
What is it?
What aren't you telling me?

545
00:34:38,908 --> 00:34:40,428
You don't understand
what you're involved in.

546
00:34:40,452 --> 00:34:42,067
I don't understand
what I'm involved in.

547
00:34:42,495 --> 00:34:44,907
I don't understand
what I'm involved in?

548
00:34:47,250 --> 00:34:48,865
What am I involved in?

549
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:51,793
If you're meeting the widow,
she leaves in three minutes.

550
00:34:53,256 --> 00:34:54,746
Ilsa: Ethan!
Ethan: I'll make it work.

551
00:34:54,841 --> 00:34:56,547
- Ethan!
- I'll make it work.

552
00:34:59,262 --> 00:35:00,468
The name's Walker.

553
00:35:00,555 --> 00:35:02,671
Yeah? You're welcome.

554
00:35:05,060 --> 00:35:06,891
(Dance music playing)

555
00:35:16,237 --> 00:35:17,272
(Beeping)

556
00:35:21,993 --> 00:35:23,054
What do you think you're doing?

557
00:35:23,078 --> 00:35:24,680
- I'm going with you.
- Like hell you are.

558
00:35:24,704 --> 00:35:25,848
People have been sent here to kill lark.

559
00:35:25,872 --> 00:35:26,872
No shit.

560
00:35:26,956 --> 00:35:29,072
No, not me. Contractors. Paid assassins.

561
00:35:29,501 --> 00:35:30,901
They don't know what he looks like,

562
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,647
they only know he's meeting
the widow at midnight.

563
00:35:32,671 --> 00:35:33,911
If you go through with this,

564
00:35:34,005 --> 00:35:36,317
they're gonna believe you're lark
and they're gonna kill you.

565
00:35:36,341 --> 00:35:37,706
How do you know all this?

566
00:35:39,511 --> 00:35:41,126
I can't tell you that.

567
00:35:43,598 --> 00:35:45,759
You should've stayed out of the game.

568
00:35:47,769 --> 00:35:49,680
You should've come with me.

569
00:35:58,113 --> 00:36:01,605
Widow: This charity was started
in honor of my mother.

570
00:36:02,283 --> 00:36:05,116
Those of you who knew her
understood her strength,

571
00:36:05,453 --> 00:36:08,115
her tenacity, her resourcefulness.

572
00:36:08,206 --> 00:36:09,206
(People laughing)

573
00:36:09,290 --> 00:36:12,032
But there was another side to her,

574
00:36:12,127 --> 00:36:14,118
a side most people never saw.

575
00:36:14,462 --> 00:36:17,920
It is that part of her spirit
that has brought us

576
00:36:18,007 --> 00:36:19,793
all together tonight.

577
00:36:20,468 --> 00:36:23,460
Max was something of a paradox.

578
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:28,222
She had a fascination for paradoxes,

579
00:36:28,977 --> 00:36:31,810
a fascination she passed on to me.

580
00:36:33,481 --> 00:36:37,815
Max had no illusions about
the world we live in today.

581
00:36:38,570 --> 00:36:41,733
But she had dreams
of a very different future.

582
00:36:42,657 --> 00:36:46,241
One in which her unique talents
were no longer required.

583
00:36:47,078 --> 00:36:49,569
All she earned from the way the world is

584
00:36:49,998 --> 00:36:53,661
went ultimately to making it
what it could someday be.

585
00:36:54,169 --> 00:36:56,660
That future isn't here yet.

586
00:36:57,881 --> 00:37:02,625
Tonight, your contributions
have brought it just a little closer.

587
00:37:02,719 --> 00:37:04,129
(Applause)

588
00:37:06,389 --> 00:37:08,129
Thank you all for coming.

589
00:37:08,224 --> 00:37:09,805
Enjoy the party.

590
00:37:13,772 --> 00:37:15,558
(Jazz music playing)

591
00:37:30,288 --> 00:37:33,405
You can't possibly be John lark.

592
00:37:36,753 --> 00:37:38,584
I'm not, actually.

593
00:37:39,422 --> 00:37:41,083
It's an alias.

594
00:37:43,676 --> 00:37:45,837
I suppose it's better than John Doe.

595
00:37:45,929 --> 00:37:47,239
Is there another name you prefer?

596
00:37:47,263 --> 00:37:49,003
Is there somewhere
we could talk privately?

597
00:37:49,098 --> 00:37:51,339
In fact I like "lark."
It does have a certain ring.

598
00:37:51,434 --> 00:37:52,536
We don't have a lot of time.

599
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:54,096
'Cause I'll be honest.

600
00:37:54,187 --> 00:37:56,519
A man of your reputation,
I was expecting someone

601
00:37:57,023 --> 00:37:58,183
uglier.

602
00:37:58,274 --> 00:37:59,274
(Gasps)

603
00:37:59,359 --> 00:38:01,691
Don't let looks deceive.
I'm as ugly as they come.

604
00:38:02,111 --> 00:38:04,523
And I'll be honest with you.
Your life is in danger.

605
00:38:06,157 --> 00:38:07,363
Don't you touch her.

606
00:38:07,450 --> 00:38:09,441
Relax. It's my brother.

607
00:38:10,703 --> 00:38:12,318
You're being rude to our guest, zola.

608
00:38:12,872 --> 00:38:14,203
It's time to go.

609
00:38:14,541 --> 00:38:16,702
Don't turn this into a scene.

610
00:38:18,586 --> 00:38:20,417
You don't want to be with this one.

611
00:38:26,970 --> 00:38:29,757
- You were saying?
- Your life is in danger.

612
00:38:30,265 --> 00:38:31,550
And who would want to kill me?

613
00:38:31,641 --> 00:38:33,097
The Americans, for starters.

614
00:38:33,268 --> 00:38:34,758
If that were true, I would know it.

615
00:38:34,936 --> 00:38:37,518
You think you're the only one
with spies in the government?

616
00:38:38,106 --> 00:38:40,939
There are people here
who don't want this meeting to happen.

617
00:38:41,276 --> 00:38:42,607
Don't believe me?

618
00:38:43,278 --> 00:38:44,609
Look around.

619
00:38:56,749 --> 00:38:58,239
I know what you're thinking.

620
00:38:58,751 --> 00:39:00,707
Maybe they're not here for you.

621
00:39:00,795 --> 00:39:02,831
Maybe they're just here for me.

622
00:39:03,172 --> 00:39:05,333
Are you willing to take that chance?

623
00:39:06,175 --> 00:39:08,166
You have something I want.

624
00:39:08,511 --> 00:39:10,718
Right now, that makes me
the only person you can trust

625
00:39:10,805 --> 00:39:12,670
to get you out of here alive.

626
00:39:13,016 --> 00:39:15,348
Or would you rather leave that
to your brother?

627
00:39:19,689 --> 00:39:23,181
I think I'd like
to go home now, Mr. lark.

628
00:39:30,366 --> 00:39:31,366
(Knife unsheathes)

629
00:39:31,701 --> 00:39:32,861
(Grunting)

630
00:39:32,994 --> 00:39:33,994
(Man groans)

631
00:39:38,291 --> 00:39:40,623
- (Both grunting)
- (People exclaiming)

632
00:39:40,919 --> 00:39:41,919
(People gasp)

633
00:39:45,006 --> 00:39:46,416
(Panicked chatter)

634
00:40:08,321 --> 00:40:09,811
- (Grunting)
(Woman yelps)

635
00:40:12,575 --> 00:40:14,406
- (Gunshot)
(People screaming)

636
00:41:13,761 --> 00:41:15,592
(Guns cocking)

637
00:41:38,119 --> 00:41:40,952
The French government took receipt
of the asset at noon today.

638
00:41:41,289 --> 00:41:43,405
Delivery will be via air
to the finance ministry

639
00:41:43,499 --> 00:41:44,699
at 8:00 A.M. tomorrow morning.

640
00:41:45,376 --> 00:41:47,207
An armored motorcade
under heavy police escort

641
00:41:47,295 --> 00:41:49,206
will transport him via this route.

642
00:41:49,714 --> 00:41:52,547
We'll create a diversion
at this intersection, here.

643
00:41:53,009 --> 00:41:56,593
The motorcade will automatically take
the preplanned alternate route here,

644
00:41:57,263 --> 00:41:59,254
where we'll extract the asset.

645
00:42:00,516 --> 00:42:02,347
Extract the asset?

646
00:42:13,446 --> 00:42:14,777
The asset.

647
00:42:16,866 --> 00:42:19,733
We paid a great deal of money
for this information.

648
00:42:19,827 --> 00:42:22,409
They gave us everything
but this man's name.

649
00:42:22,497 --> 00:42:25,034
You don't happen to know
who he is, do you?

650
00:42:26,167 --> 00:42:27,907
His name is Solomon Lane.

651
00:42:28,002 --> 00:42:30,664
British special agent turned anarchist.

652
00:42:31,672 --> 00:42:33,708
He used rogue covert operatives

653
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:36,086
to create a terror network
called the syndicate.

654
00:42:37,261 --> 00:42:40,003
Sabotage, assassination, mass murder.

655
00:42:40,348 --> 00:42:42,339
As ugly as they come.

656
00:42:43,059 --> 00:42:46,347
Walker: He was captured
by American agents two years ago.

657
00:42:46,687 --> 00:42:49,645
Since then, he's been in
a never-ending interrogation,

658
00:42:49,732 --> 00:42:51,939
passed around from
one government to another

659
00:42:53,277 --> 00:42:55,438
to answer for his crimes.

660
00:42:58,282 --> 00:42:59,772
You seem displeased, lark.

661
00:43:00,785 --> 00:43:03,447
Perhaps I didn't make myself clear.

662
00:43:04,455 --> 00:43:06,787
I came to Paris for plutonium.

663
00:43:07,125 --> 00:43:09,616
Well, there must be a misunderstanding.

664
00:43:09,710 --> 00:43:11,621
I'm just a broker.

665
00:43:11,712 --> 00:43:13,794
I connect a buyer and a seller.

666
00:43:14,465 --> 00:43:18,208
My seller's not interested in cash,
so if you want the plutonium...

667
00:43:19,053 --> 00:43:20,543
Extract Lane

668
00:43:21,305 --> 00:43:22,886
and make a trade.

669
00:43:23,391 --> 00:43:24,551
Widow: That's right.

670
00:43:29,230 --> 00:43:31,312
How do I know
the seller has what I want?

671
00:43:50,751 --> 00:43:52,833
Widow: A down payment in good faith.

672
00:43:53,671 --> 00:43:56,504
A courier will deliver
two more within 48 hours

673
00:43:56,841 --> 00:43:59,332
in exchange for him.

674
00:44:07,768 --> 00:44:08,768
All right.

675
00:44:09,645 --> 00:44:11,727
What happens after the diversion?

676
00:44:12,690 --> 00:44:14,100
(Inaudible)

677
00:45:45,449 --> 00:45:46,734
Kill everyone?

678
00:45:47,201 --> 00:45:48,441
That's your plan?

679
00:45:48,953 --> 00:45:50,784
There will be no withesses.

680
00:45:50,871 --> 00:45:53,783
What's my guarantee that Lane
walks out of this thing alive?

681
00:45:54,041 --> 00:45:55,326
He's in an armored box.

682
00:45:56,127 --> 00:45:58,038
We'll pull him out when it's safe.

683
00:45:58,713 --> 00:46:00,044
You want your plutonium,

684
00:46:00,798 --> 00:46:02,288
this is the price.

685
00:46:04,468 --> 00:46:06,754
Or do you draw the line at killing cops?

686
00:46:06,846 --> 00:46:09,053
That's John lark you're talking to.

687
00:46:12,226 --> 00:46:15,389
I murder women and children
with smallpox.

688
00:46:17,690 --> 00:46:19,430
I have no line.

689
00:46:23,654 --> 00:46:24,769
Right.

690
00:46:25,156 --> 00:46:28,148
Sleep well, everyone. Busy day tomorrow.

691
00:46:48,262 --> 00:46:50,253
Sloane: You have got to be kidding me.

692
00:46:50,598 --> 00:46:53,089
If you want Lane out of prison,
this is how it gets done.

693
00:46:53,351 --> 00:46:56,263
I wanted lark to break him out,
not Ethan hunt.

694
00:46:56,354 --> 00:47:00,188
I wanted lark at the exchange,
not Ethan hunt.

695
00:47:00,649 --> 00:47:03,391
I wanted lark to lead us
to the plutonium

696
00:47:03,486 --> 00:47:05,272
and the apostles.

697
00:47:05,363 --> 00:47:06,883
Walker: You may still get your chance.

698
00:47:07,073 --> 00:47:08,800
Have you forgotten about
the corpse we pulled

699
00:47:08,824 --> 00:47:10,260
out of the men's room
at the grand palais?

700
00:47:10,284 --> 00:47:12,070
I'm guessing that wasn't lark.

701
00:47:12,161 --> 00:47:13,571
More likely one of lark's recruits.

702
00:47:13,662 --> 00:47:15,869
Not according to our intelligence.

703
00:47:16,248 --> 00:47:18,159
Intelligence gathered by whom?

704
00:47:20,461 --> 00:47:21,792
Hunt.

705
00:47:22,630 --> 00:47:26,088
You've long held suspicions that lark
was an American agent.

706
00:47:26,175 --> 00:47:27,790
Someone who knew our every move.

707
00:47:27,885 --> 00:47:30,092
Someone who could
come and go like a ghost.

708
00:47:31,639 --> 00:47:34,130
You're suggesting hunt is John lark.

709
00:47:35,351 --> 00:47:39,344
You're reaching, Walker.
Trying to save your ass.

710
00:47:39,688 --> 00:47:41,178
It won't work.

711
00:47:41,482 --> 00:47:44,599
Think about it.
Would a man as careful as lark

712
00:47:44,693 --> 00:47:46,729
really stick his neck out like that?

713
00:47:46,821 --> 00:47:48,812
For a face-to-face with the white widow?

714
00:47:49,156 --> 00:47:51,613
- He'd send a proxy.
- A decoy.

715
00:47:51,867 --> 00:47:53,482
And if he was really smart,

716
00:47:53,577 --> 00:47:56,193
he'd have his lady friend
kill that decoy

717
00:47:56,288 --> 00:47:58,199
in front of a reliable witness.

718
00:47:58,290 --> 00:47:59,290
Me.

719
00:47:59,834 --> 00:48:02,746
The dragnet is closing in
on his terrorist alter ego.

720
00:48:03,087 --> 00:48:05,749
So he pays a man
to play the part of lark

721
00:48:05,840 --> 00:48:07,000
and has him killed.

722
00:48:07,842 --> 00:48:10,254
And under the guise
of serving his country...

723
00:48:10,594 --> 00:48:12,926
Assumes his own secret identity.

724
00:48:13,180 --> 00:48:14,590
Free to operate at will

725
00:48:14,682 --> 00:48:16,442
with the full support
of the U.S. government.

726
00:48:16,475 --> 00:48:17,681
Why?

727
00:48:18,185 --> 00:48:20,016
Why would hunt turn?

728
00:48:20,354 --> 00:48:23,346
Why did Lane do it?
Why did any of his apostles?

729
00:48:24,108 --> 00:48:26,850
They were believers in a cause.

730
00:48:27,194 --> 00:48:29,435
And when that cause
turned out to be a lie,

731
00:48:29,530 --> 00:48:32,317
they turned
against their masters.

732
00:48:32,408 --> 00:48:35,616
How many times has hunt's
government betrayed him,

733
00:48:35,703 --> 00:48:37,443
disavowed him, cast him aside?

734
00:48:37,872 --> 00:48:40,534
And how long before
a man like that

735
00:48:40,916 --> 00:48:42,406
has had enough?

736
00:48:43,043 --> 00:48:45,705
That 1s a serious accusation.

737
00:48:47,381 --> 00:48:48,871
Can you prove it?

738
00:48:52,636 --> 00:48:54,422
This is the phone
we pulled off the dead body

739
00:48:54,513 --> 00:48:55,878
at the grand palais.

740
00:49:01,270 --> 00:49:03,682
I'm guessing
it has all the proof you need.

741
00:49:51,070 --> 00:49:52,070
(Gun cocks)

742
00:50:07,461 --> 00:50:08,496
(Beeps)

743
00:50:13,717 --> 00:50:15,548
(Helicopter approaching)

744
00:51:07,605 --> 00:51:10,768
Walker: Is it true Lane gassed
a village of 2,000 people?

745
00:51:13,277 --> 00:51:14,277
Yes.

746
00:51:14,361 --> 00:51:16,818
Is it true he brought down
an entire passenger plane

747
00:51:16,905 --> 00:51:17,905
just to kill one man?

748
00:51:19,491 --> 00:51:20,651
Yes.

749
00:51:21,869 --> 00:51:23,780
- Is it true that he...
- Hey, Walker.

750
00:51:24,288 --> 00:51:26,950
Whatever you heard,
if it makes your skin crawl,

751
00:51:27,041 --> 00:51:28,622
it's probably true.

752
00:51:34,632 --> 00:51:36,122
Holy shit.

753
00:51:37,801 --> 00:51:40,042
You're the guy
that caught him, aren't you?

754
00:51:41,889 --> 00:51:42,969
How long do you think

755
00:51:43,057 --> 00:51:44,547
he's gonna keep that to himself?

756
00:51:48,646 --> 00:51:50,853
We'll burn that bridge
when we get to it.

757
00:52:40,739 --> 00:52:41,774
(Speaks French)

758
00:52:42,032 --> 00:52:43,238
(Engine starts)

759
00:52:59,174 --> 00:53:00,584
(Tires screeching)

760
00:53:40,924 --> 00:53:42,130
(Truck engine starts)

761
00:53:50,726 --> 00:53:52,136
(Tires screeching)

762
00:54:14,792 --> 00:54:16,202
(Soldiers shouting indistinctly)

763
00:54:19,296 --> 00:54:21,412
(In English) What the hell is he doing?

764
00:54:25,594 --> 00:54:27,801
- (Tires screech)
(All grunt)

765
00:54:45,030 --> 00:54:46,236
(Panicked chatter)

766
00:54:51,662 --> 00:54:53,493
(Inhaling deeply)

767
00:55:26,446 --> 00:55:28,277
(Tires screeching)

768
00:55:43,755 --> 00:55:45,040
(Scanner beeping)

769
00:55:59,354 --> 00:56:01,185
(Sirens wailing)

770
00:56:08,864 --> 00:56:10,354
(Both grunting)

771
00:56:20,626 --> 00:56:22,036
(Engine revving)

772
00:56:24,504 --> 00:56:26,415
- (Engine stalling)
(Officers shouting)

773
00:56:34,139 --> 00:56:35,720
Hunt? Where are you?

774
00:56:35,807 --> 00:56:37,547
Don't wait for me!

775
00:56:37,643 --> 00:56:40,225
- What is it? What's wrong?
- (Engine starts)

776
00:56:40,312 --> 00:56:41,722
I'll meet you at the garage.

777
00:56:47,611 --> 00:56:48,817
(Siren blares)

778
00:56:51,698 --> 00:56:53,029
Benji, do you copy?

779
00:56:53,575 --> 00:56:54,860
We copy. Go.

780
00:56:54,952 --> 00:56:58,069
Change of plan. I'm blown.
Need extraction.

781
00:56:58,163 --> 00:56:59,744
We're on our way.

782
00:57:12,928 --> 00:57:14,208
(Woman speaking French on radio)

783
00:57:14,304 --> 00:57:18,172
He's heading from notre dame to the
St. Louis bridge. Units are in pursuit...

784
00:57:52,384 --> 00:57:53,384
(Horns honking)

785
00:58:02,936 --> 00:58:04,142
(Siren wailing)

786
00:58:29,838 --> 00:58:31,203
(Truck horn blares)

787
00:58:39,139 --> 00:58:40,549
(Sirens wailing)

788
00:58:51,318 --> 00:58:52,728
(Horns honking)

789
00:59:16,885 --> 00:59:18,295
(Sirens wailing)

790
00:59:29,731 --> 00:59:31,141
(Grunting)

791
00:59:34,361 --> 00:59:36,192
(Panting)

792
00:59:38,406 --> 00:59:39,896
(Sirens wailing)

793
00:59:46,706 --> 00:59:48,196
(Car doors opening)

794
00:59:49,084 --> 00:59:50,494
(Officers shouting in French)

795
01:00:06,726 --> 01:00:08,136
(Panting)

796
01:01:00,113 --> 01:01:01,319
(Inaudible)

797
01:01:21,176 --> 01:01:23,007
(Indistinct chatter on radio)

798
01:01:38,735 --> 01:01:39,735
(Speaking French)

799
01:01:39,819 --> 01:01:40,819
Stop.

800
01:01:41,571 --> 01:01:42,777
Stay where you are.

801
01:01:43,782 --> 01:01:44,782
Get in the car.

802
01:01:45,909 --> 01:01:46,909
Nobody move.

803
01:01:50,497 --> 01:01:51,497
Show me your hands.

804
01:01:52,666 --> 01:01:53,666
(Both speaking French)

805
01:01:53,750 --> 01:01:54,956
Walk away...

806
01:01:54,960 --> 01:01:55,619
Walk away... please.

807
01:01:55,752 --> 01:01:56,332
Everyone...

808
01:01:56,336 --> 01:01:57,576
Everyone... show me your hands.

809
01:02:03,843 --> 01:02:05,424
Just walk away...

810
01:02:05,428 --> 01:02:06,543
Just walk away... please.

811
01:02:10,141 --> 01:02:11,176
(Both speaking French)

812
01:02:15,522 --> 01:02:17,183
(In English) Zola wants a word with you.

813
01:02:18,900 --> 01:02:20,310
(Groaning)

814
01:02:20,402 --> 01:02:21,402
(Both speaking French)

815
01:02:21,528 --> 01:02:22,563
What about her?

816
01:02:23,029 --> 01:02:24,029
Finish her.

817
01:02:39,963 --> 01:02:40,963
(Gunshot)

818
01:02:51,349 --> 01:02:53,180
(Groaning)

819
01:02:53,268 --> 01:02:54,383
(Speaking French)

820
01:02:54,477 --> 01:02:56,058
You'll be all right.

821
01:02:57,939 --> 01:02:59,059
(Man speaks French on radio)

822
01:02:59,190 --> 01:03:00,396
(Speaking French)

823
01:03:04,029 --> 01:03:05,519
Benji: (In English) We got to go.

824
01:03:05,613 --> 01:03:06,693
(Speaking French)

825
01:03:06,781 --> 01:03:08,612
I 'm so sorry.

826
01:03:08,616 --> 01:03:09,616
Benji: Come on.

827
01:03:18,251 --> 01:03:19,457
(Engine starts)

828
01:03:35,977 --> 01:03:37,387
(Sirens wailing)

829
01:03:45,945 --> 01:03:47,685
The name's Walker, by the way.

830
01:03:48,114 --> 01:03:50,105
Was the little car your idea?

831
01:03:59,584 --> 01:04:01,495
- (Lane groans)
- Benji: Jesus Christ!

832
01:04:02,379 --> 01:04:04,106
- What the hell was that?
- (Silenced gunshot)

833
01:04:04,130 --> 01:04:05,370
(Engine revving)

834
01:04:08,468 --> 01:04:09,674
(Tires screeching)

835
01:04:10,220 --> 01:04:12,302
- Everybody out.
- Benji: Go, go, go!

836
01:04:48,383 --> 01:04:49,873
(Horns honking)

837
01:05:02,021 --> 01:05:03,021
(Gunshot)

838
01:05:05,066 --> 01:05:06,476
(Horn blaring)

839
01:05:30,049 --> 01:05:31,630
- (Horn honking)
(Grunts)

840
01:05:42,479 --> 01:05:43,969
(Tires screeching)

841
01:05:56,075 --> 01:05:57,690
- (Brakes screech)
(Horn honks)

842
01:06:24,229 --> 01:06:25,844
(Brakes screeching)

843
01:06:26,940 --> 01:06:28,350
(Church bell tolling)

844
01:06:37,408 --> 01:06:38,739
(Shifting gears)

845
01:06:47,794 --> 01:06:48,954
(Sighs)

846
01:06:49,504 --> 01:06:50,835
That was llsa.

847
01:06:51,548 --> 01:06:52,879
Shut up.

848
01:06:53,383 --> 01:06:54,964
Very interesting.

849
01:06:58,429 --> 01:07:00,761
It's good to see you again, Ethan.

850
01:07:09,023 --> 01:07:10,103
(Groans)

851
01:07:13,444 --> 01:07:15,275
- (Panting)
- (Sirens wailing)

852
01:07:18,116 --> 01:07:19,116
(Groans)

853
01:07:37,594 --> 01:07:40,427
Oh, look who's still alive.

854
01:07:44,225 --> 01:07:46,011
There's a microwave tracker in his neck.

855
01:07:46,102 --> 01:07:47,717
Got it. You know what to do.

856
01:07:47,812 --> 01:07:50,019
Let me just assure you, this won't hurt

857
01:07:50,106 --> 01:07:51,471
enough.

858
01:07:53,735 --> 01:07:56,147
- Ninety seconds.
- (Timer ticking)

859
01:07:56,237 --> 01:07:58,157
You and your apostles think
we're gonna trade you

860
01:07:58,197 --> 01:07:59,903
for the missing plutonium.

861
01:07:59,991 --> 01:08:02,607
I'm here to tell you
that's never gonna happen.

862
01:08:02,702 --> 01:08:06,069
"Your mission, should you
choose to accept it."

863
01:08:07,081 --> 01:08:08,912
I wonder, Ethan,

864
01:08:09,000 --> 01:08:10,490
did you ever choose not to?

865
01:08:11,252 --> 01:08:12,833
Did you ever stop and ask yourself

866
01:08:12,920 --> 01:08:15,753
who it was giving you the orders or why?

867
01:08:16,549 --> 01:08:18,289
While every day the master you serve

868
01:08:18,384 --> 01:08:20,545
moves one step closer
to ending the world.

869
01:08:21,012 --> 01:08:23,128
Strange accusation
coming from a terrorist.

870
01:08:23,222 --> 01:08:24,337
Sixty seconds.

871
01:08:24,432 --> 01:08:26,468
Terrorists are schoolboys
desperate for attention,

872
01:08:26,559 --> 01:08:30,268
hoping to shape
public opinion through fear.

873
01:08:30,355 --> 01:08:33,597
I don't care in the least
what people think or feel.

874
01:08:34,025 --> 01:08:36,391
In my experience,
they don't do either for very long.

875
01:08:36,486 --> 01:08:38,631
Benji: Oh, and I suppose that
justifies bombing factories

876
01:08:38,655 --> 01:08:40,191
or bringing down civilian aircraft.

877
01:08:40,448 --> 01:08:42,814
Or strapping me
into an explosive vest!

878
01:08:42,909 --> 01:08:45,992
Consider it unfinished business,
my funny little friend.

879
01:08:46,204 --> 01:08:47,990
- Luther?
Almost there.

880
01:08:48,081 --> 01:08:50,197
Lane: You see the end
as clearly as I do, Ethan.

881
01:08:50,291 --> 01:08:53,033
Governments the world over
are descending into madness.

882
01:08:53,503 --> 01:08:57,246
The syndicate was created
to tear them down, brick by brick.

883
01:08:57,340 --> 01:08:59,331
The syndicate was
a pack of murdering cowards.

884
01:08:59,425 --> 01:09:03,088
The syndicate
was civilization's last hope!

885
01:09:03,179 --> 01:09:06,592
A chance to smash the old world order.

886
01:09:06,974 --> 01:09:08,965
That hope is gone now
because of you

887
01:09:09,394 --> 01:09:11,680
and your pathetic morality.

888
01:09:11,771 --> 01:09:13,602
(Helicopter approaching)

889
01:09:13,731 --> 01:09:15,517
You should have killed me, Ethan.

890
01:09:18,236 --> 01:09:20,101
The end you've always feared

891
01:09:20,738 --> 01:09:22,069
is coming.

892
01:09:22,615 --> 01:09:23,695
(Exhaling sharply)

893
01:09:24,492 --> 01:09:26,153
It's coming!

894
01:09:27,995 --> 01:09:30,907
And the blood will be on your hands.

895
01:09:33,251 --> 01:09:34,832
The fallout

896
01:09:35,336 --> 01:09:38,578
of all your good intentions.

897
01:09:39,048 --> 01:09:40,538
(Sirens wailing in distance)

898
01:09:43,428 --> 01:09:44,508
(Timer stops)

899
01:09:44,595 --> 01:09:46,802
- Time.
- Got it.

900
01:09:51,811 --> 01:09:53,096
(Device beeping)

901
01:09:57,442 --> 01:09:59,273
(Sirens wailing overhead)

902
01:10:02,155 --> 01:10:03,986
(Helicopter passing overhead)

903
01:10:07,785 --> 01:10:08,991
(Sirens fade)

904
01:10:11,414 --> 01:10:12,745
Get him up.

905
01:10:15,543 --> 01:10:16,908
You're mine now.

906
01:10:25,970 --> 01:10:28,211
Widow: You're just
full of surprises, lark.

907
01:10:28,306 --> 01:10:30,638
Ethan: Your brother's plan
was bad from the word go.

908
01:10:30,975 --> 01:10:32,886
You'd have lost all your men

909
01:10:32,977 --> 01:10:34,817
and Lane would've been killed
in the crossfire.

910
01:10:35,438 --> 01:10:37,099
I had to improvise.

911
01:10:37,648 --> 01:10:40,230
Widow: Well, why not say that
in the first place?

912
01:10:40,318 --> 01:10:42,104
Ethan: Because I don't
trust your people.

913
01:10:42,195 --> 01:10:44,481
Especially not your brother.

914
01:10:48,075 --> 01:10:51,067
Family. What can you do?

915
01:10:54,040 --> 01:10:56,031
So, where's Lane?

916
01:10:56,125 --> 01:10:58,366
Certainly not at the bottom
of the seine.

917
01:10:58,461 --> 01:11:00,201
I have him. He's safe.

918
01:11:00,880 --> 01:11:02,711
Where do I meet the courier?

919
01:11:04,342 --> 01:11:05,673
Let's talk about the woman.

920
01:11:08,012 --> 01:11:09,172
Woman?

921
01:11:09,430 --> 01:11:10,715
She was with you at the palais.

922
01:11:10,807 --> 01:11:12,172
Zola saw her again today.

923
01:11:12,517 --> 01:11:14,007
She tried to kill Lane.

924
01:11:14,101 --> 01:11:16,183
She had the chance to kill you,
but she didn't.

925
01:11:16,604 --> 01:11:17,604
Why?

926
01:11:21,609 --> 01:11:23,190
We have a past.

927
01:11:24,529 --> 01:11:25,860
It's complicated.

928
01:11:27,990 --> 01:11:30,322
Well, I'll make it
more complicated for you.

929
01:11:30,827 --> 01:11:32,818
My price just went up.

930
01:11:32,912 --> 01:11:35,073
Someone killed four of my men today.

931
01:11:35,164 --> 01:11:36,745
I'm assuming it was her.

932
01:11:43,089 --> 01:11:45,000
I want her, lark.

933
01:11:45,842 --> 01:11:47,582
And you're gonna bring her to me.

934
01:11:48,594 --> 01:11:50,459
Otherwise, you don't meet the courier

935
01:11:50,555 --> 01:11:52,921
and the plutonium goes
to the highest bidder.

936
01:11:54,308 --> 01:11:56,640
I'd hate for her
to come between us.

937
01:12:00,857 --> 01:12:02,188
She's yours.

938
01:12:03,067 --> 01:12:05,524
At the meeting. Not before.

939
01:12:17,999 --> 01:12:19,330
Go to London.

940
01:12:20,418 --> 01:12:22,249
Instructions will follow.

941
01:14:03,771 --> 01:14:06,638
I knew if I followed her,
you'd show up eventually.

942
01:14:06,941 --> 01:14:08,272
Are you okay?

943
01:14:10,569 --> 01:14:11,900
Lisa, I never wanted to hurt you.

944
01:14:11,988 --> 01:14:14,070
I know you have your reasons.

945
01:14:14,740 --> 01:14:15,775
I know.

946
01:14:19,912 --> 01:14:21,573
You need to walk away.

947
01:14:21,664 --> 01:14:22,995
I can't do that.

948
01:14:24,709 --> 01:14:27,246
You weren't at the palais to kill lark.

949
01:14:27,336 --> 01:14:28,451
No.

950
01:14:30,297 --> 01:14:31,833
You were there to protect him.

951
01:14:32,508 --> 01:14:33,543
Yes.

952
01:14:33,634 --> 01:14:35,420
And you killed him to protect me.

953
01:14:37,847 --> 01:14:40,179
You wanted lark to break Lane out.

954
01:14:41,809 --> 01:14:45,051
No. You needed him to break Lane out.

955
01:14:45,855 --> 01:14:47,971
Because you have to kill Lane.

956
01:14:49,358 --> 01:14:51,314
Who's making you do this?

957
01:14:52,945 --> 01:14:54,526
Mig.

958
01:14:57,158 --> 01:14:58,158
Why?

959
01:14:58,409 --> 01:15:00,240
After we captured him in London,

960
01:15:00,327 --> 01:15:03,615
they tried to bring Lane home
through diplomatic channels.

961
01:15:03,706 --> 01:15:06,368
But too many countries
want their pound of flesh.

962
01:15:06,459 --> 01:15:08,370
A man like that, what he's seen,

963
01:15:08,461 --> 01:15:10,022
what he knows
about British intelligence,

964
01:15:10,046 --> 01:15:13,413
they can't have him talking
to a foreign government ever.

965
01:15:13,507 --> 01:15:15,168
That's not what I'm asking.

966
01:15:16,135 --> 01:15:17,466
Why did they send you?

967
01:15:18,554 --> 01:15:20,966
This is how I prove my loyalty.

968
01:15:21,682 --> 01:15:23,172
This is how I come home.

969
01:15:23,267 --> 01:15:25,053
But you were out.

970
01:15:25,144 --> 01:15:26,554
You were free.

971
01:15:26,645 --> 01:15:28,385
We are never free.

972
01:15:29,190 --> 01:15:32,023
I spent two years undercover with Lane.

973
01:15:32,109 --> 01:15:34,816
To them, I'm as much
of a threat as he is.

974
01:15:36,030 --> 01:15:39,363
I kill him, or I never stop running.

975
01:15:41,660 --> 01:15:44,072
Now tell me where he is.

976
01:15:48,709 --> 01:15:50,574
I can't help you.

977
01:15:50,669 --> 01:15:53,376
I will get to him one way or another.

978
01:15:54,465 --> 01:15:56,956
Please don't make me go through you.

979
01:16:34,922 --> 01:16:35,922
(Gasps)

980
01:16:44,932 --> 01:16:46,342
(Cell phone ringing)

981
01:16:53,023 --> 01:16:54,138
Yes.

982
01:16:54,233 --> 01:16:56,019
Widow: (On phone)
Are you here in London?

983
01:16:56,110 --> 01:16:57,395
Ethan: I am.

984
01:16:57,486 --> 01:16:59,477
Are you ready to meet the courier?

985
01:17:00,156 --> 01:17:02,317
Yes. Where do I go?

986
01:17:02,658 --> 01:17:04,364
Where would you like to meet?

987
01:17:42,531 --> 01:17:43,531
Mr. secretary.

988
01:17:44,700 --> 01:17:46,782
I prayed to god that it wasn't true.

989
01:17:46,869 --> 01:17:48,450
Benji: Well, in his defense, sir,

990
01:17:48,537 --> 01:17:49,993
if Ethan hadn't intervened,

991
01:17:50,080 --> 01:17:51,474
a great many people
would have been killed.

992
01:17:51,498 --> 01:17:53,739
Yes, Dunn, I'm sure that
the good people of Paris

993
01:17:53,834 --> 01:17:56,997
and the nation of France as a whole
will take that into account.

994
01:17:58,130 --> 01:17:59,791
So what the hell happened?

995
01:18:06,722 --> 01:18:08,587
- (Device hisses)
(Exhales)

996
01:18:13,062 --> 01:18:14,268
(Device beeping)

997
01:18:19,068 --> 01:18:21,525
At which point, we were
told to come to London

998
01:18:22,196 --> 01:18:23,686
and await further instructions.

999
01:18:23,948 --> 01:18:25,279
And what happens now?

1000
01:18:26,075 --> 01:18:27,155
Now,

1001
01:18:28,202 --> 01:18:29,783
we meet the widow in 20 minutes.

1002
01:18:29,870 --> 01:18:31,360
She'll take us to a courier

1003
01:18:31,455 --> 01:18:34,538
who'll hand over our missing plutonium
in exchange for Solomon Lane.

1004
01:18:34,625 --> 01:18:36,206
Or, in our scenario,

1005
01:18:37,419 --> 01:18:38,659
Benji.

1006
01:18:39,088 --> 01:18:40,203
Jesus.

1007
01:18:40,589 --> 01:18:41,624
I'm sorry, what?

1008
01:18:41,715 --> 01:18:43,318
Ethan: Luther and I are gonna
take you to the courier.

1009
01:18:43,342 --> 01:18:45,022
Walker stays here
and guards the real Lane.

1010
01:18:45,094 --> 01:18:46,174
Absolutely not.

1011
01:18:46,262 --> 01:18:47,614
Wait, wait.
Why do I have to be Lane?

1012
01:18:47,638 --> 01:18:48,638
Benji.

1013
01:18:48,722 --> 01:18:51,555
Our mission, my mission,
is to recover that plutonium,

1014
01:18:51,642 --> 01:18:53,724
and I will do so at any cost.

1015
01:18:53,811 --> 01:18:55,472
Even if I have to trade Lane.

1016
01:18:55,562 --> 01:18:56,972
The real Lane.

1017
01:18:57,064 --> 01:18:59,100
And I will never let him go.

1018
01:18:59,191 --> 01:19:02,183
When the apostles realize
that you're playing games,

1019
01:19:02,278 --> 01:19:04,564
you'll lose the plutonium. Again.

1020
01:19:04,947 --> 01:19:06,653
You let us worry about the apostles.

1021
01:19:06,740 --> 01:19:09,152
As it stands, we have a bigger problem.

1022
01:19:09,243 --> 01:19:10,699
A bigger problem?

1023
01:19:11,453 --> 01:19:12,943
- Llsa.
- Benji: Lisa?

1024
01:19:13,038 --> 01:19:14,574
Our Lisa? Llsa faust Lisa?

1025
01:19:14,665 --> 01:19:15,850
How is she mixed up in all of this?

1026
01:19:15,874 --> 01:19:18,206
She's been ordered
to kill Lane. Direct from MI6.

1027
01:19:18,294 --> 01:19:21,707
Look, wait. So that was her
in Paris? On the bike.

1028
01:19:21,797 --> 01:19:22,832
Yeah.

1029
01:19:22,923 --> 01:19:24,129
Ethan, she tried to kill us!

1030
01:19:24,216 --> 01:19:25,485
- Ethan: No, not us. Not us.
Yeah.

1031
01:19:25,509 --> 01:19:27,750
Lane. She tried to kill Lane.
She has no choice.

1032
01:19:27,845 --> 01:19:28,880
And she will kill me!

1033
01:19:29,054 --> 01:19:30,156
I'm not gonna let that happen.

1034
01:19:30,180 --> 01:19:32,260
Ethan, how exactly are you
not gonna let that happen?

1035
01:19:33,767 --> 01:19:35,974
- I'm working on it.
- Oh, he's working on it.

1036
01:19:36,061 --> 01:19:37,497
Ethan: Right now,
we don't have a lot of time.

1037
01:19:37,521 --> 01:19:39,040
We have to get ready for this meeting.

1038
01:19:39,064 --> 01:19:40,520
Hunley: The meeting is a trap.

1039
01:19:41,734 --> 01:19:43,816
The white widow is working with the CIA.

1040
01:19:43,902 --> 01:19:45,438
She has been since the beginning.

1041
01:19:46,322 --> 01:19:49,359
Bargaining for immunity
is her stock-in-trade.

1042
01:19:49,450 --> 01:19:51,987
Capturing the plutonium,
and the apostles, and John lark

1043
01:19:52,077 --> 01:19:54,534
buys her a lot of goodwill
with the Americans.

1044
01:19:54,621 --> 01:19:57,488
But if Sloane knew the meeting was
a trap, why didn't she just tell us?

1045
01:19:57,583 --> 01:19:59,686
Hunley: Because, in her mind,
anybody could be John lark,

1046
01:19:59,710 --> 01:20:01,450
including one of us.

1047
01:20:02,671 --> 01:20:04,707
And now her suspicions are confirmed.

1048
01:20:07,217 --> 01:20:08,627
According to that dossier,

1049
01:20:08,719 --> 01:20:11,176
a trail of electronic evidence
