01:37:57,036 --> 01:37:58,321
Know when you're beat.

1302
01:38:04,377 --> 01:38:05,583
(Elevator bell dings)

1303
01:38:10,550 --> 01:38:11,960
(Grunting)

1304
01:39:09,859 --> 01:39:11,499
Luther: These are the designs
we recovered

1305
01:39:11,569 --> 01:39:13,730
from Dr. delbruuk's lab in Berlin.

1306
01:39:13,821 --> 01:39:15,903
Benji: That's a five-megaton
nuclear device.

1307
01:39:15,990 --> 01:39:17,676
That's greater than
all the explosive energy

1308
01:39:17,700 --> 01:39:18,735
released in world war il.

1309
01:39:18,826 --> 01:39:22,489
To disarm it, normally
we'd cut the fuse wire here.

1310
01:39:22,580 --> 01:39:24,036
What, "normally"?

1311
01:39:24,123 --> 01:39:26,956
Walker and Lane
have two plutonium cores,

1312
01:39:27,043 --> 01:39:28,408
meaning two bombs.

1313
01:39:28,753 --> 01:39:31,039
Yeah. And they're both linked
by a microwave fail-safe

1314
01:39:31,130 --> 01:39:32,983
which is accurate to
within one-tenth of a second.

1315
01:39:33,007 --> 01:39:37,171
Any attempt to defuse one bomb
automatically triggers the other.

1316
01:39:37,470 --> 01:39:40,303
Meaning once armed,
the bombs cannot be disarmed.

1317
01:39:40,389 --> 01:39:43,051
Benji: The countdown is
started by a remote detonator,

1318
01:39:43,142 --> 01:39:45,133
which 1s also a fail-safe.

1319
01:39:45,228 --> 01:39:47,514
Meaning once the countdown starts,

1320
01:39:48,189 --> 01:39:49,520
it can't be stopped.

1321
01:39:51,108 --> 01:39:53,690
So the solution to this is?

1322
01:39:55,696 --> 01:39:57,186
We're working on it.

1323
01:39:58,783 --> 01:39:59,783
So,

1324
01:40:00,451 --> 01:40:02,863
technically, this is a suicide mission.

1325
01:40:13,965 --> 01:40:14,965
What is it?

1326
01:40:15,550 --> 01:40:17,882
Have a seat. Please.

1327
01:40:21,889 --> 01:40:23,880
In all the years
that I've known Ethan,

1328
01:40:24,225 --> 01:40:26,887
he's only been serious
about two women.

1329
01:40:27,979 --> 01:40:29,719
One was his wife.

1330
01:40:30,481 --> 01:40:31,812
He's married?

1331
01:40:32,024 --> 01:40:34,015
No, he was.

1332
01:40:34,402 --> 01:40:36,142
Was? What happened to her?

1333
01:40:36,487 --> 01:40:37,852
Well, she was taken

1334
01:40:38,239 --> 01:40:40,901
by some people
who wanted to get to Ethan.

1335
01:40:41,075 --> 01:40:43,782
It's okay,
he got her back in one piece.

1336
01:40:44,412 --> 01:40:45,948
Then he quit the game.

1337
01:40:46,956 --> 01:40:49,117
They were happy for a while.

1338
01:40:49,584 --> 01:40:52,542
But every time something bad
happened in the world,

1339
01:40:52,712 --> 01:40:55,124
Ethan would think,
"I should've been there."

1340
01:40:55,381 --> 01:40:57,963
And she would wonder,
"who's watching the world

1341
01:40:58,050 --> 01:41:00,041
"while Ethan's watching me?"

1342
01:41:00,469 --> 01:41:03,632
Deep down, they both knew
that someday, somehow,

1343
01:41:03,806 --> 01:41:06,798
something truly terrible
was going to happen

1344
01:41:08,269 --> 01:41:10,476
all because they were together.

1345
01:41:11,564 --> 01:41:12,644
So...

1346
01:41:15,026 --> 01:41:17,768
- Where is she now?
- She's a ghost.

1347
01:41:17,987 --> 01:41:19,318
Good at it, too.

1348
01:41:19,572 --> 01:41:21,233
Taught her myself.

1349
01:41:21,574 --> 01:41:23,940
Every now and then,
she sends up a signal

1350
01:41:24,035 --> 01:41:25,195
to let Ethan know she's safe.

1351
01:41:25,953 --> 01:41:27,864
And that keeps him going.

1352
01:41:29,206 --> 01:41:30,696
Why are you telling me this?

1353
01:41:32,543 --> 01:41:33,658
Hmm.

1354
01:41:34,629 --> 01:41:38,213
We're in this mess because
Ethan wouldn't let me die.

1355
01:41:40,801 --> 01:41:42,166
He's a good man.

1356
01:41:42,803 --> 01:41:46,512
And he cares about you
more than he can admit.

1357
01:41:47,642 --> 01:41:51,305
That's one more worry
than he can handle right now.

1358
01:41:53,898 --> 01:41:55,980
If you care about him,

1359
01:41:56,567 --> 01:41:58,057
you should walk away.

1360
01:42:01,572 --> 01:42:02,937
Luther...

1361
01:42:03,032 --> 01:42:04,522
Ethan: Is everything all right?

1362
01:42:11,582 --> 01:42:12,617
(Sighs softly)

1363
01:42:16,796 --> 01:42:18,502
I'm coming with you.

1364
01:42:27,473 --> 01:42:28,588
I know.

1365
01:42:32,728 --> 01:42:34,093
So how do we find him?

1366
01:42:35,815 --> 01:42:37,476
Microwave transponder.

1367
01:42:37,650 --> 01:42:40,357
Traceable via satellite
anywhere in the world.

1368
01:42:40,695 --> 01:42:42,422
Lane had one of these
in the back of his neck.

1369
01:42:42,446 --> 01:42:43,446
(Rapid beeping)

1370
01:42:43,531 --> 01:42:44,646
We removed it in Paris.

1371
01:42:44,907 --> 01:42:47,068
At the same time,
we put our own transponder in.

1372
01:42:47,243 --> 01:42:48,323
Got it.

1373
01:42:50,287 --> 01:42:52,528
Luther: 36-hour delayed activation,

1374
01:42:52,707 --> 01:42:55,119
in case Lane's apostles scan him.

1375
01:42:55,876 --> 01:42:57,867
So you planned on letting him go.

1376
01:42:58,045 --> 01:43:00,127
Not this way, but yes.

1377
01:43:00,381 --> 01:43:01,917
He's gonna lead us to the plutonium.

1378
01:43:02,216 --> 01:43:03,797
How can you be sure?

1379
01:43:03,968 --> 01:43:06,050
His plan to put me in prison
went to hell.

1380
01:43:07,221 --> 01:43:09,382
Now he's gonna want me there
for the end.

1381
01:43:09,890 --> 01:43:11,471
So when does this transponder activate?

1382
01:43:11,559 --> 01:43:13,161
Benji: I got him. I got him,
I got him, I got him!

1383
01:43:13,185 --> 01:43:15,267
He's traveling east
over Europe at 500 knots.

1384
01:43:15,438 --> 01:43:16,438
Luther: He's airborne.

1385
01:43:16,605 --> 01:43:17,720
Shall we inform the CIA?

1386
01:43:18,315 --> 01:43:19,725
The CIA's been infiltrated.

1387
01:43:19,942 --> 01:43:22,308
I don't trust anybody
outside of this room.

1388
01:43:22,820 --> 01:43:24,481
We're gonna have to go it alone.

1389
01:43:27,366 --> 01:43:28,366
So where do we go?

1390
01:43:48,763 --> 01:43:50,094
Ethan: How we doing, Benji?

1391
01:43:50,556 --> 01:43:53,218
If there's a way to defuse these bombs,
I can't find it.

1392
01:43:53,392 --> 01:43:55,633
You'll figure it out.
I know you will.

1393
01:43:56,020 --> 01:43:57,100
(Steady beeping)

1394
01:43:57,229 --> 01:43:59,561
Luther: Damn. Ethan, we lost the signal.

1395
01:43:59,940 --> 01:44:01,555
Lane must've found our transmitter.

1396
01:44:01,942 --> 01:44:05,275
- What's his last position?
Luther: About 30 miles northeast.

1397
01:44:05,529 --> 01:44:07,520
Then that's where he wants us to go.

1398
01:44:07,698 --> 01:44:09,529
- What's there?
- The nubra river valley.

1399
01:44:09,700 --> 01:44:11,406
There's only a medical camp there.

1400
01:44:11,494 --> 01:44:13,860
Humanitarian aid overseas.

1401
01:44:14,205 --> 01:44:16,947
Why would Lane target a medical camp?

1402
01:44:17,583 --> 01:44:18,583
Smallpox.

1403
01:44:19,251 --> 01:44:20,251
What?

1404
01:44:20,336 --> 01:44:23,578
Smallpox. The apostles triggered
a smallpox outbreak in kashmir.

1405
01:44:24,089 --> 01:44:26,705
Lane must've wanted that camp there
for a reason.

1406
01:44:26,967 --> 01:44:28,298
But what?

1407
01:44:28,844 --> 01:44:30,926
- Oh, my god.
“what is it?

1408
01:44:31,764 --> 01:44:34,847
The nubra river is at the base
of the siachen glacier.

1409
01:44:35,184 --> 01:44:36,744
So a nuclear blast there
would irradiate

1410
01:44:36,769 --> 01:44:39,852
the largest natural irrigation system
in the world.

1411
01:44:40,523 --> 01:44:44,186
Fresh water from the border of
China to India and Pakistan.

1412
01:44:45,820 --> 01:44:48,311
They're gonna starve one-third
of the world's population.

1413
01:44:48,489 --> 01:44:49,695
"The greater the suffering..."

1414
01:44:49,949 --> 01:44:51,940
"The greater the peace."

1415
01:44:52,493 --> 01:44:55,326
I still don't understand
why Lane wants a medical camp there.

1416
01:44:55,496 --> 01:44:56,656
Ethan: It doesn't matter.

1417
01:44:56,831 --> 01:44:59,413
All that matters now is we find a way
to defuse those bombs.

1418
01:44:59,500 --> 01:45:01,240
Uh, I think I've found it.

1419
01:45:01,585 --> 01:45:03,075
Maybe. Um...

1420
01:45:03,170 --> 01:45:05,690
Look, there appears to be a flaw
in the bomb's operating system.

1421
01:45:05,840 --> 01:45:08,001
The remote detonator
requires that firing key.

1422
01:45:08,175 --> 01:45:10,507
If we remove that key,
then it should short out

1423
01:45:10,594 --> 01:45:13,006
the fail-safe and allow us
to cut both fuses.

1424
01:45:13,180 --> 01:45:14,699
So one of us needs to get the detonator

1425
01:45:14,723 --> 01:45:15,723
and remove that key.

1426
01:45:15,808 --> 01:45:16,843
Benji: Yeah.

1427
01:45:17,017 --> 01:45:19,759
While the rest of us cut the fuses
on both bombs. Simple.

1428
01:45:20,604 --> 01:45:21,889
Yeah, but...

1429
01:45:22,273 --> 01:45:23,604
But what?

1430
01:45:23,899 --> 01:45:26,060
Well, in order to make this work,

1431
01:45:26,151 --> 01:45:28,267
we can't remove the key
or cut the fuses

1432
01:45:28,445 --> 01:45:31,107
until after the countdown starts.

1433
01:45:31,699 --> 01:45:33,439
Ilsa: But Walt,
just so I've got this clear.

1434
01:45:33,617 --> 01:45:36,108
Our only chance
to safely defuse both bombs

1435
01:45:36,203 --> 01:45:38,068
1s to let the countdown start.

1436
01:45:39,039 --> 01:45:41,530
And then remove that key.

1437
01:45:49,633 --> 01:45:50,964
Okay.

1438
01:46:03,689 --> 01:46:04,769
(Whirring)

1439
01:46:07,735 --> 01:46:08,895
(Beeping)

1440
01:46:09,028 --> 01:46:12,361
Lane: Both devices are now
connected to the detonator.

1441
01:46:13,449 --> 01:46:15,405
Fifteen minutes should
give you enough time

1442
01:46:15,492 --> 01:46:17,574
to reach minimum safe distance.

1443
01:46:19,997 --> 01:46:22,158
My running days are over.

1444
01:46:23,083 --> 01:46:25,324
This is where it ends for me.

1445
01:46:51,862 --> 01:46:53,272
(Device beeping)

1446
01:46:53,989 --> 01:46:56,071
I'm getting signals all over the place.

1447
01:46:56,241 --> 01:46:59,608
We're at a medical camp.
X-ray machines, cat scanners,

1448
01:46:59,703 --> 01:47:01,103
radiological signatures everywhere.

1449
01:47:01,246 --> 01:47:02,736
It's like a needle in a haystack.

1450
01:47:02,831 --> 01:47:04,787
Process of elimination, one at a time.

1451
01:47:04,875 --> 01:47:06,661
Let's split up. Stay on comms.

1452
01:47:08,420 --> 01:47:09,830
(Beeping continues)

1453
01:47:12,758 --> 01:47:14,749
(Indistinct announcements over pa)

1454
01:47:17,012 --> 01:47:18,047
Julia: Ethan?

1455
01:47:23,894 --> 01:47:24,974
Julia?

1456
01:47:29,858 --> 01:47:31,143
Is that...

1457
01:47:35,406 --> 01:47:36,486
Man: Julia!

1458
01:47:38,409 --> 01:47:39,740
Does he know?

1459
01:47:40,911 --> 01:47:41,911
Man: Hey.

1460
01:47:42,621 --> 01:47:44,703
Uh, this is my husband, Erik.

1461
01:47:45,040 --> 01:47:46,120
Uh, this is...

1462
01:47:46,208 --> 01:47:47,869
rob. rob Thorne.
Dr. rob Thorne.

1463
01:47:48,627 --> 01:47:50,618
- L worked with Julia...
- At mass general.

1464
01:47:51,380 --> 01:47:52,380
Before New York.

1465
01:47:52,464 --> 01:47:53,795
Oh, you're kidding. (Chuckles)

1466
01:47:53,966 --> 01:47:55,706
- What a coincidence!
- L know. I...

1467
01:47:55,884 --> 01:47:57,715
- What brings you all this way?
- L was, uh...

1468
01:47:57,886 --> 01:47:59,797
I was in turtuk, not far from here

1469
01:48:00,055 --> 01:48:02,546
and heard help was needed.

1470
01:48:02,808 --> 01:48:03,808
Oh, well,

1471
01:48:03,976 --> 01:48:05,932
actually we're just about finished here.

1472
01:48:06,020 --> 01:48:08,477
The whole village is inoculated.
But, uh...

1473
01:48:09,064 --> 01:48:10,804
What were you doing out in turtuk?

1474
01:48:11,483 --> 01:48:12,973
rob's on vacation.

1475
01:48:13,152 --> 01:48:15,814
No. No, I'm... I'm working.

1476
01:48:18,198 --> 01:48:19,859
You're a long way from home.

1477
01:48:20,117 --> 01:48:22,233
Yeah, yeah.
Thanks to our guardian angel.

1478
01:48:23,037 --> 01:48:24,037
Guardian?

1479
01:48:24,288 --> 01:48:25,932
Well, yeah. We were
running a field hospital

1480
01:48:25,956 --> 01:48:28,038
outside of Darfur when
the outbreak happened here.

1481
01:48:28,208 --> 01:48:29,310
And here comes this phone call

1482
01:48:29,334 --> 01:48:30,995
from an anonymous donor,
out of the blue.

1483
01:48:31,795 --> 01:48:33,273
And, uh, he says
he's ready to underwrite

1484
01:48:33,297 --> 01:48:35,788
the entire operation. One condition.

1485
01:48:36,258 --> 01:48:37,748
We run the whole thing.

1486
01:48:37,968 --> 01:48:39,799
Erik: (Chuckles softly)
Can you believe that?

1487
01:48:40,971 --> 01:48:42,461
I certainly can.

1488
01:48:42,890 --> 01:48:44,380
Yeah. Out of the blue.

1489
01:48:44,558 --> 01:48:45,968
Out of the blue.

1490
01:48:48,479 --> 01:48:49,969
That's quite a full life.

1491
01:48:50,147 --> 01:48:52,138
Yeah, you know, before Julia,
I never traveled.

1492
01:48:52,399 --> 01:48:54,060
- (Beeping)
- I never even left New York.

1493
01:48:54,234 --> 01:48:55,920
- Never left the hospital.
- (Beeping intensifies)

1494
01:48:55,944 --> 01:48:58,481
Seven days a week,
dusk till dawn. No vacations.

1495
01:48:58,655 --> 01:49:00,145
Ethan, I think I found something.

1496
01:49:02,284 --> 01:49:03,569
Heart attack at 55.

1497
01:49:03,744 --> 01:49:06,656
And she convinced me
to let it all go.

1498
01:49:07,331 --> 01:49:08,992
Help where it's needed most.

1499
01:49:09,166 --> 01:49:11,202
So we've been on the go ever since,

1500
01:49:11,502 --> 01:49:13,333
and I've never been more fulfilled.

1501
01:49:14,505 --> 01:49:16,166
I'm happy for you.

1502
01:49:17,257 --> 01:49:18,417
Erik: Thank you.

1503
01:49:20,427 --> 01:49:22,133
- Well, we should get going.
- Erik: Oh.

1504
01:49:22,221 --> 01:49:23,586
We have a lot of packing to do.

1505
01:49:23,680 --> 01:49:25,762
Oh, no, I'll handle that.
You two should catch up.

1506
01:49:25,849 --> 01:49:27,510
Oh, no, I should
get out of your hair.

1507
01:49:27,684 --> 01:49:29,724
(Chuckles) Are you kidding?
You should stick around.

1508
01:49:29,853 --> 01:49:32,060
I'm just sorry you came
all this way for nothing.

1509
01:49:32,856 --> 01:49:33,891
Um...

1510
01:49:34,316 --> 01:49:36,648
Tell you what, we'll pack,

1511
01:49:36,944 --> 01:49:38,855
and why don't we give you
a ride back to turtuk,

1512
01:49:38,946 --> 01:49:41,437
you two can catch up
in the car? Yeah?

1513
01:49:41,907 --> 01:49:43,397
You're very kind.

1514
01:49:44,326 --> 01:49:46,658
Settled. See you soon.

1515
01:49:46,745 --> 01:49:48,110
(Indistinct announcements over pa)

1516
01:49:48,205 --> 01:49:49,695
It was good to see you. (Chuckles)

1517
01:49:50,999 --> 01:49:53,832
(Whispers) I am so sorry, Julia.
I'm so sorry.

1518
01:50:09,101 --> 01:50:10,511
(Indistinct chatter)

1519
01:50:15,107 --> 01:50:17,018
Take both helicopters.

1520
01:50:18,193 --> 01:50:19,854
No one else leaves.

1521
01:50:27,953 --> 01:50:29,614
Benji: Careful, careful, careful.

1522
01:50:34,376 --> 01:50:35,376
Luther: It's armed.

1523
01:50:35,460 --> 01:50:36,940
But the countdown hasn't started yet.

1524
01:50:37,004 --> 01:50:38,773
The network signal's strong,
which means the other device

1525
01:50:38,797 --> 01:50:40,333
is close by and the detonator.

1526
01:50:40,507 --> 01:50:42,839
About half a k in that direction.

1527
01:50:44,052 --> 01:50:45,462
They're still here.

1528
01:50:46,930 --> 01:50:48,170
Luther, you keep working on it.

1529
01:50:48,223 --> 01:50:49,338
You two, come with me.

1530
01:50:50,976 --> 01:50:53,308
Oh, sure. I got this.

1531
01:50:53,729 --> 01:50:55,720
Don't worry about old Luther.

1532
01:51:17,961 --> 01:51:18,961
(Beeping)

1533
01:51:29,765 --> 01:51:31,096
Ethan: Walker.

1534
01:51:35,103 --> 01:51:36,593
(Beeping)

1535
01:51:36,772 --> 01:51:37,772
Luther: Damn.

1536
01:51:37,981 --> 01:51:39,312
Ethan, the countdown has started!

1537
01:51:39,399 --> 01:51:40,479
We have 15 minufes.

1538
01:51:40,651 --> 01:51:42,312
Walker has the detonator.

1539
01:51:46,073 --> 01:51:47,073
(Engine starts)

1540
01:51:52,079 --> 01:51:53,194
Come on, come on!

1541
01:51:55,415 --> 01:51:56,825
We have to evacuate these people.

1542
01:51:56,917 --> 01:51:57,917
There's no time.

1543
01:51:58,085 --> 01:52:00,326
This whole valley's gonna be
incinerated in 15 minutes.

1544
01:52:04,341 --> 01:52:05,456
Ilsa: It's too late!

1545
01:52:05,717 --> 01:52:06,752
Ethan: No.

1546
01:52:07,052 --> 01:52:08,337
I'm gonna get the detonator.

1547
01:52:08,720 --> 01:52:10,551
- What? How?
- I'll figure it out.

1548
01:52:11,598 --> 01:52:13,589
Find Lane!
Find the other bomb!

1549
01:52:14,851 --> 01:52:17,211
- [ What the hell is he doing?
- ] Find it best not to look.

1550
01:52:49,386 --> 01:52:50,876
(Devices beeping)

1551
01:52:52,764 --> 01:52:53,844
How we doing, Luther?

1552
01:52:54,057 --> 01:52:55,910
Tripwires everywhere.
I don't have enough hands.

